'''Soliant Health''' is a healthcare staffing company that provides medical staff to various healthcare facilities throughout the United States. The company is based in [[Atlanta, Georgia]].<ref name=BLOOM/>
==History== In November 1991, Soliant Health was founded as Elite Medical by David Alexander, with the company initially specializing in travel healthcare.<ref name=PRnews>{{cite news|title=MPS Group Outlines Healthcare Staffing Strategy; Launches Soliant Health Brand and Names David Alexander President|url=http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/mps-group-outlines-healthcare-staffing-strategy-launches-soliant-health-brand-and-names-david-alexander-president-74631212.html|accessdate=24 October 2015|agency=[[PR Newswire]]|date=11 March 2003}}</ref> Alexander interpreted a model set by retailer [[Nordstrom]] as a way to reduce [[Turnover (employment)|turnover]] among his staff by boosting their morale, which in turn would increase the confidence of the healthcare workers they provided.<ref name=INC>{{cite web|last1=Mochari|first1=Ilan|title=What You Learn on the Other Side|url=http://www.inc.com/magazine/20021101/24833.html|website=''[[Inc. (magazine)|Inc.]]''|accessdate=24 October 2015}}</ref> In July 2002, Elite Medical was acquired by [[Adecco Group North America]] (then MPS Group Inc.) and was rebranded in March 2003 as Soliant Health, with David Alexander appointed as its president.<ref name=PRnews/>
==''Most Beautiful Hospitals''== Since 2009, Soliant Health has ranked "The 20 Most Beautiful Hospitals" in the United States.<ref name=SHbeaut1>{{cite web|last1=Tuten|first1=Tera|title=The 20 Most Beautiful Hospitals in the U.S. (2015) are…|url=http://blog.soliant.com/most-beautiful-hospitals/2015/|website=Soliant Health|accessdate=24 October 2015}}</ref> On their first year making the rankings on the 2009 list, Soliant Health cited a February 2009 by the [[University of Michigan School of Public Health]] that one of the factors that made patients happy was the appearance of the hospital.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Winter|first1=Ryan|title=Soliant Health’s 20 Most Beautiful Hospitals in the U.S. Rankings for 2009|url=http://blog.soliant.com/most-beautiful-hospitals/2009/|website=Soliant Health|accessdate=24 October 2015}}</ref>
The 2015 list includes:<ref name=SHbeaut1/> {{columns-list|colwidth=18em| # Phoebe Sumter Medical Center # Homestead Hospital # Forest Park Medical Center # Riverside Regional Medical Center # [[HealthPark Medical Center]] # St. Anthony Regional Hospital & Nursing Home # Forest Park Medical Center # Elmhurst Memorial Hospital # Doctors Memorial Hospital # Mercy Health West Hospital # Baylor, Scott & White Hillcrest Medical Center # [[Logan Regional Hospital]] # West Shore Hospital # Forest Park Medical Center # Children’s Hospital of Pittsburgh of UPMC # Southwestern Virginia Mental Health Institute # Adirondack Health # [[Riverview Medical Center]] # [[Flagler Hospital]] #La Rabida Children’s Hospital and Cuyuna Regional Medical Center }}
